Package exception

Defines a set of exception for being used within all the project.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidOperationException
    Exception used inside RVM launched when the argument type does not correspond with the command - Example: operation ADD for non-numeric stackable arguments.
    NoLabelFoundException
    Exception used inside RVM to declare when there is no of the required label defined in the code.
    NotInitializedException
    Exception used inside RVM to warn when the variable has not been previously initialized.
    OutOfBoundsException
    Exception used inside RVM to declare when we exceed the access to a vector,
    SegmentationFaultException
    Exception used inside RVM launched when going out of bounds inside the stack - Example: requiring 2 arguments when there is only one in the stack).
    StackUnderflowException
    Exception used inside Stack for indicating Stack Underflow.
    UndefinedFunctionException
    Exception used inside RVM to declare when there is no of the required label defined in the code.
    WrongTypeException
    Exception used inside RVM to declare when there is no of the required label defined in the code.
